HEADWORD: Felucca
<hw>Fe*luc"ca</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>feluca</ets> (cf. Sp. <ets>faluca</ets>, Pg. <ets>falua</ets>), fr.
Ar. <ets>fulk</ets> ship, or <ets>harr⟦amac⟧qah</ets> a sort of
ship.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A small, swift-sailing vessel,
propelled by oars and lateen sails, -- once common in the
Mediterranean.</def> <note>Sometimes it is constructed so that the helm
may be used at either end.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

